Build native installers: .exe, .dmg, and .AppImage

Package the desktop app into a proper installer per platform instead of a raw
PyInstaller folder/zip.

- Windows: build/windows-installer.iss + build-windows.ps1 compile an Inno
  Setup installer (dist/Athena Dictate Setup.exe) with Start-menu/desktop
  shortcuts and a per-user (no-admin) install. The script skips the installer
  gracefully if Inno Setup isn't installed.
- macOS: build-macos.sh packs the .app into dist/Athena Dictate.dmg via hdiutil,
  with an Applications drag-target.
- Linux: build-linux.sh assembles an AppDir (AppRun + .desktop + icon) and runs
  appimagetool to produce dist/Athena Dictate.AppImage.
- CI: install Inno Setup on the Windows runner; build scripts now emit the final
  installers directly, so the workflow just uploads them (and attaches them to
  releases on a tag). if-no-files-found is now an error so a missing installer
  fails the build loudly.
- README: document the new installer outputs.

